16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2239.1 of Title 74, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The following purchases by the Oklahoma Tourism and
21 Recreation Department shall be exempt from the Oklahoma Central
22 Purchasing Act:
23 1. Merchandise for resale purchased for and sold over the
24 Internet, in publications or through Department retail outlets, such
Req. No. 12608 Page 1

1 as l odges, gift shops, golf course pro shops, restaurants, and other
2 purchases made for the production of such merchandise; and
3 2. Materials, supplies, and services necessary for the
4 efficient and economical operation of revenue generating, Department
5 operated facilities and programs, including those made to maintain
6 or improve guest perception of quality and service including, but
7 not limited to, mattresses, pillows, bed skirts, drapery, small
8 appliances customary in hospitality spaces such as hotel or lodge
9 rooms and cabins, pool equipment, and pool maintenance costs.
10 B. The Department is authorized to promote state-owned, leased,
11 or operated facilities. The Department may utilize specific
12 promotion programs such as the provision of complimentary rooms,
13 package-rate plans, group rates, guest incentive sales programs,
14 entertainment of prospective guests, employee-information programs,
15 golf promotional programs as well as other sales and promotion
16 programs considered acceptable in the hospitality industry, in the
17 travel industry, or the regional magazine industry are approved as
18 necessary advertising and promotion expenses.
19 C. For purposes of this section, "revenue generating" means a
20 purchase that would affect the ability to generate revenue at a
21 Department operated facility or program. Revenue generated by the
22 agency is built into the Department's budget to fund operational
23 expenses and salaries. Loss of revenue will require the agency to
24 reduce staff or seek additional funding to cover the loss created by
